      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is simply an object meant to provide begin() and end() Iters to the range-for loop.\n\nIf it weren\u0027t private, I would just suggest adding begin() and end() methods to SkPath itself:\n\n for (auto [verb, pts, w] : skPath) {\n     ...\n }\n\nOther options could be:\n\n for (auto [verb, pts, w] : skPath.priv()) // (Requires converting SkPathPriv to non-static)\n for (auto [verb, pts, w] : SkPathPriv::WalkPath(skPath))\n for (auto [verb, pts, w] : SkPathPriv::Iterate(skPath))\n for (auto [verb, pts, w] : SkPathPriv::Visit(skPath))\n\nAny preferences? I kind of like \"Iterate\".\n\nHowever, I think the name \"Iter\" should be reserved for the object returned by begin()/end().",
